# CONCEPT_BOUNDARY.md

## Purpose

Define the design-stage concept boundary for {{ project.name }}.

This optional template describes what the concept may discuss at a generalized level. It does not define runtime behavior, implementation architecture, device integration, or live target interaction.

## Scope

- Generalized concept purpose and non-goals.
- Synthetic/mock-only assumptions.
- Input and output category boundaries.
- Design evidence boundaries.
- Owner-review dependencies.

## Source Use

Use only source rows approved for design summary. Owner-review sources must remain unused until the owner accepts, revises, or defers them. Excluded sources must remain outside the target.

| source row | decision | use in this document |
|---|---|---|
| SRC-### | usable for design summary | TBD |
| SRC-### | owner review required | Not used unless resolved |
| SRC-### | excluded from repo | Not used |

## Prohibited Content

- Runtime implementation or executable behavior.
- Application source code.
- C# source, solution, project, XAML, build assets, scripts, or binaries.
- PLC/device code.
- Live target write support, start/stop/reset, mode change, or external mutation.
- GitHub Actions or cloud CI.
- Raw source bulk copy.
- IP, port, tag value, live parameter, secret, private input, live config, account, credential, or equipment detail.

## Approval Boundary

This concept boundary supports design-only review. It does not approve implementation planning, runtime work, profile creation, example creation, render integration, gate implementation, or live target interaction.

## Review Checklist

- Concept scope is generalized and domain-neutral.
- Synthetic/mock-only boundary is explicit.
- No live target or device behavior is described.
- No implementation artifacts are implied.
- Source-use decisions are followed.
- Prohibited content is absent.
